    • Class cosc202.andie.Emboss1

      class Emboss1 extends Object implements Serializable

      • Serialized Fields

        • kernelValues
          float[] kernelValues

          Applies the Emboss filter to an input BufferedImage.

          A convolution is applied to the image using a unique kernel. Every pixel's final colour value is influenced by the colour values of neighbouring pixels. The degree to which the neighbouring pixels affect the colour is specified in a kernel.

          This emboss goes from top left to bottom right.

        • highlightedArea
          Rectangle2D highlightedArea
          Deselects mouse region
        • ohye
          double ohye
        • scale
          double scale

          The zoom-level of the current view. A scale of 1.0 represents actual size; 0.5 is zoomed out to half size; 1.5 is zoomed in to one-and-a-half size; and so forth.

          Note that the scale is internally represented as a multiplier, but externally as a percentage.
